Test Cases for Compliance & Audit Copilot

Below are test cases derived from the updated user stories. They cover primary functionality, normal scenarios, and failure or edge scenarios, while staying within the defined scope only.

User Story 1: Monitor Regulatory Updates

User Story
As a Compliance Officer, I want the system to monitor relevant regulatory sources, so that I can stay informed about new or modified compliance requirements.

Test Case 1.1 — Successful retrieval of regulatory updates

Objective: Validate that the system retrieves updates from configured regulatory sources.

Preconditions:

Regulatory sources are configured in the system.

At least one source contains a new or modified regulatory update.

Steps:

Start the regulatory monitoring process.

Check the list of retrieved updates.

Expected Result:

The system retrieves updates from configured regulatory sources.

New or modified regulatory requirements are identified and displayed for review.

Test Case 1.2 — No new regulatory updates available

Objective: Validate system behavior when no new updates are present.

Preconditions:

Regulatory sources are configured.

No new or modified updates exist in the sources.

Steps:

Start the regulatory monitoring process.

Review the monitoring results.

Expected Result:

The system completes monitoring successfully.

No new updates are displayed.

The result clearly indicates that no new or modified regulatory requirements were found.

Test Case 1.3 — Configured regulatory source unavailable

Objective: Validate system behavior when a configured source cannot be reached.

Preconditions:

At least one regulatory source is configured but unavailable.

Steps:

Start the regulatory monitoring process.

Review the monitoring results.

Expected Result:

The system does not retrieve updates from the unavailable source.

The system indicates that the source could not be accessed.

Available sources, if any, are still processed.

User Story 2: Review Regulatory Changes

User Story
As a Compliance Analyst, I want to review identified regulatory updates, so that I can understand which regulatory changes may impact our organization.

Test Case 2.1 — View structured regulatory update details

Objective: Validate that identified updates are presented in a structured format.

Preconditions:

At least one regulatory update has been identified by the system.

Steps:

Open the list of identified regulatory updates.

Select one regulatory update for review.

Expected Result:

The selected update is shown in a structured format.

The details clearly indicate the relevant regulation being updated.

Test Case 2.2 — Review multiple regulatory updates

Objective: Validate that the analyst can review more than one update.

Preconditions:

Multiple regulatory updates have been identified.

Steps:

Open the list of identified regulatory updates.

Review each update one by one.

Expected Result:

Each regulatory update can be viewed separately.

Each update shows its relevant regulation clearly.

Test Case 2.3 — Attempt to review updates when none exist

Objective: Validate system behavior when no updates are available for review.

Preconditions:

No regulatory updates have been identified.

Steps:

Open the regulatory updates section.

Expected Result:

The system shows that no regulatory updates are available for review.

No incomplete or blank update details are displayed.

User Story 3: Generate Compliance Reports

User Story
As a Compliance Officer, I want the system to generate structured compliance reports, so that I can document the organization’s compliance status for audits.

Test Case 3.1 — Successful compliance report generation

Objective: Validate that the system generates a structured compliance report using available compliance information and applicable regulatory requirements.

Preconditions:

Compliance information is available.

Applicable regulatory requirements are available.

Steps:

Trigger compliance report generation.

Open the generated report.

Expected Result:

The system generates a structured compliance report.

The report summarizes applicable regulations.

The report includes the organization’s current compliance status.

Test Case 3.2 — Generate report with limited compliance information

Objective: Validate behavior when some compliance information is missing.

Preconditions:

Applicable regulatory requirements are available.

Only partial compliance information is available.

Steps:

Trigger compliance report generation.

Review the generated report.

Expected Result:

The system generates a structured report using available information.

The report includes the current compliance status based on available data.

Missing information is not falsely presented as complete.

Test Case 3.3 — Attempt report generation with no available data

Objective: Validate behavior when neither compliance information nor applicable regulatory requirements are available.

Preconditions:

No compliance information is available.

No applicable regulatory requirements are available.

Steps:

Trigger compliance report generation.

Expected Result:

The system does not produce a misleading report with invented content.

The system indicates that report generation cannot be completed due to unavailable input data.

User Story 4: Detect Compliance Gaps

User Story
As a Compliance Analyst, I want the system to identify potential compliance gaps, so that I can address areas where current documentation or processes may not meet regulatory requirements.

Test Case 4.1 — Successful detection of compliance gaps

Objective: Validate that the system flags areas where regulatory requirements do not match existing compliance documentation.

Preconditions:

Regulatory requirements are available.

Compliance documentation is available.

At least one mismatch exists.

Steps:

Trigger compliance gap detection.

Review identified gaps.

Expected Result:

The system analyzes regulatory requirements and available compliance information.

The system flags areas where requirements do not match compliance documentation.

The compliance analyst can review the identified gaps.

Test Case 4.2 — No compliance gaps found

Objective: Validate behavior when compliance documentation matches regulatory requirements.

Preconditions:

Regulatory requirements are available.

Compliance documentation is available.

No mismatch exists.

Steps:

Trigger compliance gap detection.

Review the result.

Expected Result:

The system completes the analysis successfully.

No compliance gaps are flagged.

The result clearly indicates that no gaps were found.

Test Case 4.3 — Gap detection with missing compliance documentation

Objective: Validate behavior when required compliance documentation is unavailable.

Preconditions:

Regulatory requirements are available.

Compliance documentation is missing or incomplete.

Steps:

Trigger compliance gap detection.

Review the result.

Expected Result:

The system analyzes available information only.

The system flags mismatches only where comparison is possible.

The result indicates that complete gap analysis may be limited due to missing documentation.

User Story 5: Support Audit Preparation

User Story
As an Audit Manager, I want access to compliance reports and identified compliance gaps, so that I can prepare for internal or external compliance audits.

Test Case 5.1 — Access compliance reports for audit preparation

Objective: Validate that the audit manager can access generated compliance reports.

Preconditions:

At least one compliance report has been generated.

Steps:

Log in as Audit Manager.

Open the compliance reports section.

Select a report.

Expected Result:

The audit manager can access generated compliance reports.

The selected report is available for review.

Test Case 5.2 — Access identified compliance gaps for audit preparation

Objective: Validate that the audit manager can review identified compliance gaps.

Preconditions:

Compliance gaps have been identified.

Steps:

Log in as Audit Manager.

Open the compliance gaps section.

Review the listed gaps.

Expected Result:

The audit manager can access identified compliance gaps.

The identified gaps are available for review as supporting material for audit preparation.

Test Case 5.3 — Audit manager attempts access when no reports or gaps exist

Objective: Validate behavior when audit preparation materials are not available.

Preconditions:

No compliance reports have been generated.

No compliance gaps have been identified.

Steps:

Log in as Audit Manager.

Open the compliance reports section.

Open the compliance gaps section.

Expected Result:

The system indicates that no compliance reports are available.

The system indicates that no compliance gaps are available.

No invalid or empty artifacts are shown as if they were valid outputs.